article.headline: St. Peter's 57, Iona 48
article.story: JERSEY CITY, N.J. -- Nick Leon scored 17 points and Wesley Jenkins added 16 points and 11 rebounds as St. Peter's defeated Iona 57-48 Friday night. St. Peter's (10-18, 7-10 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference) never trailed, but Iona (12-17, 7-10) kept the game close through the first half, trailing 23-20 at intermission. St. Peter's stretched its lead to 13 points late in the second half, taking advantage of cold shooting by Iona. The Gaels shot only 30 percent for the game, including 3-of-17 from 3-point range. The Gaels' Gary Springer led all scorers with 18 points and had a game-high 12 rebounds. Ryan Bacon was also in double figures for the Peacocks, with 13 points.
